Ruckersville was first listed as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusVA/>

As of the [[census]] of 2010, there were 1,141 people, 461 households, and 316 families residing in the CDP. The [[population density]] was {{convert|414.9|/sqmi|/km2|disp=preunit|people&nbsp;|people|abbr=out}}. There were 512 housing units at an average density of {{convert|186.2|/sqmi|/km2|disp=preunit|people&nbsp;|people|abbr=out}}. The racial makeup of the town was 85.5% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 6.9% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.6% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 1.1% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 2.7% [[Race (United States Census)|some other race]], and 3.2% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 6.1% of the population.<ref name="Census 2010 DP">{{cite web |url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/SF1DP1/1600000US5169360 |title=Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Census Summary File 1 (DP-1): Ruckersville CDP, Virginia |publisher=U.S. Census Bureau |work=American Factfinder |accessdate=March 29, 2017 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213152155/https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/SF1DP1/1600000US5169360 |archive-date=February 13, 2020 |url-status=dead }}</ref>

There were 461 households in the CDP, out of which 30.6% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 52.5% were headed by [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 10.8% had a female householder with no husband present, and 31.5% were non-families. 26.5% of all households were made up of individuals, and 8.2% were someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.48, and the average family size was 2.93.<ref name="Census 2010 DP" />

In the CDP, 23.0% of the population were under the age of 18, 7.1% were from age 18 to 24, 22.8% were from 25 to 44, 28.6% were from 45 to 64, and 18.5% were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 43.5 years. For every 100 females there were 96.0 males, and for every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 94.0 males.<ref name="Census 2010 DP" />

For the period 2011–15, the estimated median annual income for a household in the CDP was $53,962, and the median income for a family was $68,043.<!--No data: Male full-time workers had a median income of $ versus $ for females.--> The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $24,082.<!--Margins of error too high to report: About x% of families and y% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including z% of those under age 18 and w% of those age 65 or over.--><ref>{{cite web |url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/15_5YR/DP03/1600000US5169360 |title=Selected Economic Characteristics: 2011-2015 American Community Survey 5-Year Estimates (DP03) |publisher=U.S. Census Bureau |work=American Factfinder |accessdate=March 29, 2017 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213113027/https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/15_5YR/DP03/1600000US5169360 |archive-date=February 13, 2020 |url-status=dead }}</ref>

